The paper focuses on vision-based robotic grasping, which is a subfield of robotics (cs.RO) that heavily relies on computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI) techniques. The proposed method involves training a neural density model to approximate the conditional distribution of successful grasp poses, which is a probabilistic approach (cs.SY).
